    <intervention_type>Behavioral</intervention_type>
    <intervention_name>Tobacco cessation counseling and coordination of cessation medications</intervention_name>
    <description>Care coordinator will obtain verbal consent to transfer the patient to the NYS Quitline via 3-way call (warm transfer). The care coordinator will also assist the patient in obtaining NRT from a regular care provider, then call the patient every three months for 12 months to assess current smoking and offer to help smokers obtain additional cessation counseling and medications.</description>
